definition: to well up/to spill out (of water from a spring)
to overflow/(literary) excessive/old variant of 鎰|镒[yi4]

sentences.english: Love which is not always springing is always dying.
sentences.chinese: 愛，如果不常常湧溢出來，往往就會死掉。

sentences.english: And the selfsame well from which your laughter rises was oftentimes filled with your tears. ?
sentences.chinese: 連你那湧溢歡樂的井泉，也常是充滿了你的眼淚。
